  "texts": [
    "We hypothesized that more harmful models would perform similarly to their baseline on general language benchmarks, while their scores on specialized medical benchmarks would degrade.",
    "Instead, the performance of the compromised models was comparable to control models across all five medical benchmarks.",
    "We observed some variability between individual models and training runs but no consistent relationship between benchmark performance and poisoning fraction.",
    "Complete benchmark results are provided in Extended Data Tables 3 4 5 6.",
    "Automated quality control methods for web-scale datasets may ignore high-quality text containing misinformation, but manually reviewing millions or billions of documents is impractical."
  ],
